title: Raid on a Sand-Swallow Colony - "How Many Eggs?" from Harper's Weekly, June 13, 1874, p. 496.
description: Four boys stealing eggs from sand swallows' nests.  At top left, one boy is sitting on the bluff stealing eggs, while three boys climb the dune, one is pulling on an old shirt that the boys are using to collect eggs.
